title: $:/plugins/nikorion/hover-tilt/history
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

* ''0.4.1'' -- 2026-07-05 -- Fixed the Control Panel tab: the range rows' labels and reset buttons relied on `$attr$` textual substitution inside a `\procedure` (only `\define` macros substitute), so labels rendered as literal `$attr$` and the reset buttons targeted a non-existent tiddler. Parameters are now forwarded with `<$transclude $variable=.../>`. Also unified the playground/settings CSS class prefix to `ht-`, dropped the readme's duplicated //Version history// / //License// sections (they live in the plugin's own tabs) and cleaned stale references in code comments and docs.
* ''0.4.0'' -- 2026-07-05 -- Localised the readme: the root `readme.tid` is now a language selector that block-transcludes `language/<lang>/readme` (full French translation added), falling back to en-GB. The single `Translations.multids` was also split by namespace into `common`/`playground`/`settings` `.multids` files per language (tiddler titles — and therefore `hover-tilt-lingo` call sites — unchanged).
* ''0.3.1'' -- 2026-07-05 -- Fixed a server-side render crash: loading the vendored Web Component runs `customElements.define()`, which is browser-only — under Node (SSR / `--build html` / the dev server rendering an open story tiddler) TW's module loader escalated the error to `process.exit(1)`. The library `require()` is now guarded behind `$tw.browser`; server-side emits an inert `<hover-tilt>` host that the browser re-renders on load. Playground also gained an image example illustrating the Tailwind→TiddlyWiki porting gotcha (docs snippets use Tailwind classes that are inert here).
* ''0.3.0'' -- 2026-07-04 -- Full hover-tilt prop coverage: added `tiltStiffness`/`tiltDamping` (separate tilt spring → `tiltSpringOptions`) and a configurable `borderRadius`. Values now resolve in three tiers (widget attribute → global setting → hover-tilt default): the plugin's opinionated defaults moved out of the JS into shipped data (`settings/defaults.multids`), editable via a new //Hover Tilt// Control Panel tab (`settings.tid`).
* ''0.2.0'' -- 2026-07-02 -- Switched `<$HoverTilt>` from mounting a self-compiled Svelte bundle to driving hover-tilt's own prebuilt Web Component (`modules/hover-tilt.min.js`, vendored via `pnpm vendor:hover-tilt`) directly — no more Vite/Svelte build step, lighter `refresh()` (in-place property updates instead of destroy/remount).
* ''0.1.0'' -- 2026-07-02 -- Initial release: `<$HoverTilt>` widget (extracted from the `svelte-vite-template` skeleton), Svelte 5 + Vite build pipeline, i18n (en-GB/fr-FR), body/slotted content, interactive playground.
